                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/4861: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-11-23T10:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 23, 1925—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 23—1:01 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>493. American consul, Swatow, states that it is reported Canton Government
                    contemplates taking over Maritime Customs, Swatow. He asks whether action
                    similar to that of the consul general, Canton, on the same question in 1923
                    should be taken.<note n="58" xml:id="d618fn58">See <ref
                            target="frus1923v01#pg_551">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1923, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 551</ref> ff.</note> Please
                    instruct.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
